reviewText:
Outstanding treatment of a difficult time in America
Hats off to Julie Lynch!!

Well since there's only two reviews, you need to watch it! Hard to speak of the acting since there was a little budget. I'm sure it was fun to make. Julie Lynch had a sexual crush on Christine, this was clear.
but an amazing independent film in the tradition of the great New York Movies. Christine Harnos is giving a heart wrenching and daring performance.

Director Julie Lynch takes us back to when we all started to worry about HIV Aids in our free wheeling lives. Her shots of the city brought real world credibility to the picture. The main characters all did a tremendous job in portraying the personalities and characteristics that many of us had lived during that time. Thouroughly enjoyed the film! TimT
